OL,6,FLidl has joined the string of
OL,7,Fsupermarket chains rationing fruit and
OL,8,Fvegetables as retailers attempt to
OL,9,Fbattle the nationwide shortage of
OL,10,Fpopular fresh produce.
OL,12,FThe budget chain is restricting sales
OL,13,Fof peppers, tomatoes and cucumbers to
OL,14,Fthree per customer, citing a "recent
OL,15,Fincrease in demand".
OL,17,FIt comes after Tesco, Aldi, Asda and
OL,18,FMorrisons all introduced similar
OL,19,Frestrictions as consumers around the
OL,20,Fcountry faced empty pallets due to the
OL,21,Fvegetable shortage.
OL,3,CLidl follows Tesco and Morrisons in
OL,4,Crationing peppers and tomatoes
